Report: Are Social Media Cleanses Effective? 1. Definition and Purpose: Social media cleanses involve intentional breaks from social media usage to mitigate negative psychological effects. 2. Empirical Evidence: Research links social media usage to anxiety and depression; detox users report mood improvements. 3. User Experiences: Anecdotal evidence shows users feel liberated and more focused post-detox. 4. Challenges: Effectiveness relies on individual commitment and sustainable behavior change. 5. Recommendations: Set achievable goals and reflect on the experience. 6. Conclusion: Social media cleanses benefit mental health but sustaining their effects requires ongoing commitment.